  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nanvil 0.1.0 (9256265 2023-01-13T02:41:01.751014Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nAbstract: If the Anvil node ran in fork mode and we mined a block in this node, we call **getBalance** or **getCode** at the fork block number, an BlockOutOfRangeError will be raised.\r\n\r\nSteps:\r\n\r\n1. Run Anvil instance:\r\n````\r\nanvil --fork-url https://rpc.vvs.finance\r\n````\r\n\r\n2. Run a hardhat console\r\n````\r\nyarn hardhat console\r\n````\r\n\r\n3. Run the following code in the console\r\n````\r\nprovider = new ethers.providers.JsonRpcProvider('http://localhost:8545/')\r\nforkBlockNumber = (await provider.send(\"anvil_nodeInfo\", [])).forkConfig.forkBlockNumber\r\n\r\nawait provider.send(\"eth_getBalance\", [\"0xea01e309146551a67366fe9943E9Ed83Ae564057\", '0x' + (Number(forkBlockNumber)).toString(16)])\r\n// Respond successfully\r\n\r\nawait provider.send(\"evm_mine\")\r\n\r\nawait provider.send(\"eth_getBalance\", [\"0xea01e309146551a67366fe9943E9Ed83Ae564057\", '0x' + (Number(forkBlockNumber)).toString(16)])\r\n// Respond error: {\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":57,\"error\":{\"code\":-32602,\"message\":\"BlockOutOfRangeError: block height is 6466479 but requested was 6466478\"}}'\r\n````\r\n\r\n* I tried the Hardhat node, and it has no such issue.\r\n\r\n",
